# UI, accessibility, and styling

- Semantic-classes-first: Use design system classes (`.heading-*`, `.body-*`, `.btn-*`, `.card-*`, `.badge-*`, `.container-*`). Utilities allowed only for micro-spacing inside leaf components (e.g., `gap-1–2`, `mt-1–2`) and must not override typography or colors.
- Semantics: Prefer semantic elements (button, nav, header, section) over generic div.
- Keyboard: Ensure focus states and keyboard navigation for interactive components.
- Images: Provide meaningful `alt`; use Next Image with sizes/quality helpers from `utils/image-quality.ts`.
- Forms: Label controls and associate `htmlFor` properly; validate before submit.
- Headless UI: Use `@headlessui/react` for accessible patterns where needed.
- Colors: Never use Tailwind `gray-*`; use semantic tokens (`foreground`, `foreground-strong`, `muted`, `border`, `primary`). Use opacity suffixes like `/80` for hierarchy (Tailwind v3+ syntax).
- Focus: Prefer `:focus-visible`; use `.focus-ring` / `.focus-ring-error` utilities from globals. Ensure keyboard-only users see clear focus outlines.
- Reduced motion: Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` (animations/transitions dampened globally via globals.css snippet).
- Layout: Use semantic containers: `.container-page` (wide/listing), `.container-article` (reading/detail), `.container-form` (narrow forms). Keep horizontal padding via `px-section-x`.
